<p>
    The High Performance Computing Centre (HPCC) at Federal Institute of Science 
    and Technology (FISAT), Angamaly, Kerala, India, was set up in the year 2007. 
    The centre is primary a research centre under the Department of Computer 
    Science at FISAT. HPCC focusses on research and consultancy work in Cluster 
    computing using free and open source technology. The HPCC has Dhakshina-II a 
    40 noded cluster running on Debian Lenny. There are two IBM X series servers 
    and 40 execution nodes, all having Debian as the base operating system. The 
    primarily used software are OpenMPI, OpenLDAP, OCTAVE Parallel and Ganglia.
</p>

<p>
    Debian was chosen for its 'free' nature and stability.
</p>
